  "resource_type_specific": "EEG Dataset",
  "description": "This dataset comprises EEG recordings from an exogenous attention task designed to investigate the neural mechanisms of attentional control and memory integration. Participants performed a structured experimental paradigm involving exogenous cueing while continuous EEG signals were recorded. The study examined how external cues modulate neural activity during cognitive tasks, with a focus on the interaction between attention and working memory processes. The dataset is part of a larger research initiative on memory anticipation and cognitive control.",
